description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hampshire Primary Care Psychological Therapy Service – italk Step 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Counselling for Depression (CfD) Therapist trainee&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;italk is an exciting, transformative and expanding psychological therapies service within which to work. We are commissioned by North Hampshire, West Hampshire, South East Hampshire and Fareham &amp; Gosport CCGs to deliver the IAPT services in these communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a strong partnership service; comprised of a collaboration between Southern Health NHS Foundation Trust and Solent Mind charity. We strive to deliver a high quality, evidence-based, patient-centred therapy service, to the population of Hampshire. We are looking for highly-motivated and passionate individuals, trained in Person-centred or Humanstic counselling or Psychotherapy. The successful post-holders will complete training in Person-centred Experiential Counselling for Depression (PCE-CfD) and deliver high quality therapeutic interventions to our local residents. Applications for Counsellors already qualified in PCE-CfD are welcome, and may progress within this role to complete supervisors training when eligible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;italk is comprised of 3 ‘strands&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. &lt;strong&gt;italk core&lt;/strong&gt;, delivers evidence based psychological therapeutic interventions for our local population in Hampshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2. &lt;strong&gt;italk health&lt;/strong&gt;, italk work in collaboration with local health services including community respiratory, musculoskeletal, perinatal and diabetes teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3. &lt;strong&gt;italk@work&lt;/strong&gt;, offers a range of services to enable organisations and industries to support the emotional wellbeing of their employees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are dedicated to delivering superb quality assessment and evidence-based interventions, with the patient always at the heart of our offer. The range of psychologically focused therapies we deliver include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Step 2: Guided self-help, Psycho-education groups, (guided/unguided) computerised CBT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Step 3: Cognitive Behavioural Therapy (CBT), Interpersonal Therapy (IPT), Mindfulness Based Cognitive Therapy (MBCT), Cognitive Analytic Therapy (CAT), Compassion Focused Therapy (CFT), Comprehend, Cope and Connect (CCC), Eye Movement Desensitisation and Reprocessing (EMDR), Counselling for Depression (CfD) and Couples Therapy. These therapies are delivered through a stepped care service model and italk operate as an established Improving Access to Psychological Therapies (IAPT) Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At italk, patients are at the heart of what we do. We are a passionate and supportive team, dedicated to improving mental health in our local communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service delivers a stepped care IAPT model as a partnership, with Solent Mind providing Step 2 interventions and SHFT delivering treatments at Step 3. Together, we enable over 1,500 patients each month to feel like themselves again.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Step 2 work includes outreach to ensure our local communities know we’re here for them when they need us, psychoeducational groups and workshops to equip patients with healthy coping skills, and guided self-help to empower patients to achieve their recovery goals independently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Step 3 team enable patients to recover from common mental health conditions, using evidence-based treatments tailored to the individual needs and recovery goals of our patients. Our therapists practice evidence based psychological interventions in both individual and group settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our therapists have opportunities to pursue their professional specialisms through programmes like our Long-Term Conditions pathways, work with the Ministry of Defence, Primary Care Networks, and co-facilitated groups with Health Visitors for new mothers experiencing postnatal mental health conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Does this sound like a service you could strengthen and thrive in?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, we look forward to receiving your application, and you joining our team to support patients within Hampshire. We currently have vacancies across the three Clusters within italk;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;South West: Eastleigh, Romsey, Southern Parishes, New Forest&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;South East: Bordon, Petersfield, Havant, Fareham and Gosport&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mid &amp; North: Winchester, Andover, Basingstoke, Alton&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should be familiar with the values of the NHS Constitution, and the visions of Southern Health; to improve patient and user experience, to improve outcomes for patients and carers, and finally, reducing our costs to ensure that we operate in the most efficient manner possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to find out more about these posts please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amy Francis&lt;/strong&gt; (Clinical Lead Service Manager): amy.francis@southernhealth.nhs.uk / 07500992109&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Charlotte Winfield&lt;/strong&gt; (Clinical Lead Service Manager): &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;charlotte.winfield@nhs.net/: 07979531016&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job advert will be closing 8th November 2020.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will take place week commencing 16th November 2020. Interview dates may be flexible/held remotely dependent on COVID-19 government restrictions in place at the time.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
